name: Lover
description: When you play this card, immediately pay an amount of food equal to the number of complete rounds left to play to take a "Family Growth Even without Room" action.

name: Basket Carrier
description: Once each harvest, you can buy 1 wood, 1 reed, and 1 grain for 2 food total.

name: Cesspit
description: Alternate placing 1 clay and 1 wild boar on each remaining round space, starting with clay. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Brewery Pond
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" or "Reed Bank" accumulation space, you also get 1 grain and 1 wood.

name: Forest Clearer

description: If you play this card in round 4 or before, place 4 wood and 4 clay on the space for round 9. At the start of this round, you get the resources.

name: Nail Basket
description: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, you can place 1 stone from your supply on that space (for the next visitor) to take a ‚ÄúBuild Fences‚Äù action.

name: Small-scale Farmer
description: As long as you live in a house with exactly 2 rooms, at the start of each round, you get 1 wood.

name: Stone House Reconstruction
description: At any time, you can renovate your clay house to a stone house withot placing a person. (You must pay the normal renovation cost.)

name: Christianity
description: When you play this card, all other players get 1 food each.

name: Haydryer
description: Immediately before each harvest, you can buy 1 cattle for 4 food minus 1 food for each pasture you have. (The minimum cost is 0).

name: Forest Stone
description: Place 2 food on this card. Each time you use a wood accumulation space, move 1 of these food to your supply. Each time you use a stone accumulation space, add 2 food to this card.

name: Granary
description: Place 1 grain each on the remaining spaces for rounds 8, 10, and 12. At the start of these rounds, you get the grain.

name: Sheep Provider
description: Each time any player (including you) uses the "Sheep Market" accumulation space, you get 1 grain.

name: Ranch Provost
description: If there are still 3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 2/3/4 wood. During scoring, each player with a pasture of highest capacity gets 3 bonus points.

name: Nave
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each of the 5 columns of your farmyard board containing at least one room.

name: Cherry Orchard
description: This card is a field on which you can only sow and harvest wood as you would grain. Each time you harvest the last wood from this card, you also get 1 vegetable.

name: Maintenance Premium
description: Place 3 food on this card. Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get 1 food from this card. Each time you renovate restock this card to 3 food.

name: Plow Hero
description: Each time you use the "Farmland" or "Cultivation" action space with the first person you place in a round, you can plow 1 additional field for 1 food.

name: Chick Stable
description: Add 3 and 4 to the current round and place 2 food on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Hutch
description: Place 0, 1, 2, and 3 food in this order on the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Value Assets
description: After each harvest, you can buy exactly one of the following goods: 1 Food ‚Üí 1 Wood; 1 Food ‚Üí 1 Clay; 2 Food ‚Üí 1 Reed; 2 Food ‚Üí 1 Stone

name: Tree Farm Joiner
description: Place 1 wood on each of the next 2 odd-numbered round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the wood and, immediately afterward, a "Minor Improvement" action.

name: Stockyard
description: This card can hold up to 3 animals of the same type. (It is not considered a pasture).

name: Shepherd's Whistle
description: At the start of the breeding phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1 unfenced stable without animal, you get 1 sheep.

name: Animal Tamer
description: When you play this card, you immediately get your choice of 1 wood or 1 grain. Instead of just 1 animal total, you can keep any 1 animal in each room of your house.

name: Cubbyhole
description: For each room that you add to your house, place 1 food from the general supply on this card. At the start of each feeding phase, you get food equal to the amount on this card.

name: Agrarian Fences
description: Each time you use the "Grain Utilization" action space, you can take a "Build Fences" action instead of one of the two actions provide by the action space.

name: Basket Weaver
description: When you play this card, immediately build the "Basketmaker's Workshop" major improvement for 1 stone and 1 reed.

name: Stone Sculptor
description: Each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 stone for 1 bonus point and 1 food.

name: Dairy Crier
description: When you play this card, each player (including you) can choose to get 2 sheep or 2 food; you also get 1 cattle.

name: Saddler
description: Each time after you build a major improvement, you can pay 1 food to plow 1 field.

name: Throwing Axe
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space while there is at least 1 wild boar on the "Pig Market" accumulation space, you also get 2 food.

name: Sleight of Hand
description: When you play this card, you can immediately exchange up to 4 building resources for an equal number of other building resources.

name: Water Gully
description: Place 1 cattle, 1 grain, and 1 cattle on the next 3 round spaces (in that order). At the start of these rounds, you get the good.

name: Clay Hut Builder
description: Once you no longer live in a wooden house, place 2 clay on each of the next 5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the clay.

name: Open Air Farmer
description: When you play this card, you remove exactly 3 stables in your supply from play to build a pasture covering 2 farmyard spaces. You only need to pay a total of 2 wood for fences

name: Greening Plan
description: During scoring, if you then have at least 2/4/5/6 unplanted fields, you get 1/2/3/5 bonus points.

name: Acquirer
description: At the start of each round, you may pay food equal to the number of people you have to buy 1 good of your choice from the general supply.

name: Scales
description: Each time after you place an improvement or occupation in front of you, if you then have the same number of improvements and occupations in play, you get 2 food.

name: Bucksaw
description: Each time you renovate, you can also pay 1 wood to get 1 bonus point and 1 grain.

name: Fir Cutter
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 food. Each time after you use an animal accumulation space with your 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th person, you get 1/1/2/2/3 wood.

name: Butter Churn
description: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 food for every 3 sheep and 1 food for every 2 cattle you have.

name: Trident
description: If you play this card in round 3/6/9/12, you immediately get 3/4/5/6 food.

name: Oriental Fireplace
description: At any time: Vegetable ‚Üí 4 Food; Sheep ‚Üí 3 Food; Cattle ‚Üí 5 Food "Bake Bread" action: Grain ‚Üí 2 Food

name: Adoptive Parents
description: For 1 food, you can take an action with offspring in the same round you get it. If you do, the offspring does not count as "newborn".

name: Private Forest
description: Place 1 wood on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the wood.

name: Drudgery Reeve
description: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 wood. During scoring, each player with 1+/2+/3+ building resources of each type gets 1/3/5 bonus points.

description: Harvest: [<GRAIN>+<VEG>] -(1x)-> 6<FOOD> Scoring: 1/2/3 [<GRAIN>+<VEG>] -(1x)-> 2/4/6<SCORE>

description: Each returning home phase in which no player returns a person from a "Lessons" action space, you can play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 food.

name: Mattock
description: Each time you get reed and/or stone from an action space, you get 1 additional clay.

name: Shoreforester
description: When you play this card and each time 1 reed is placed on an empty "Reed Bank" accumulation space in the preparation phase, you get 1 wood.

name: Overhaul
description: Immediately raze all of your fences, add up to 3 fences from your supply, and rebuild them. (You do not lose any animals during this.)

name: Reed-Hatted Toad
description: Add 5, 7, 9, 11, and 13 to the current round and place 1 reed on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the reed.

name: Hawktower
description: Place a stone room on round space 12. If you live in a stone house at the start of the round, you can build the stone room at no cost. Otherwise, discard the stone room.

name: Homekeeper
description: Exactly one clay or stone room in your house can hold an additional person if the room is adjacent to both a field and a pasture.

name: Elder Baker
description: This card is an action space for you only. When you use it, you get 3 grain. You can build the "Stone Oven" major improvement even when taking a "Minor Improvement" action.

name: Mud Wallower
description: Each time you use an accumulation space, place 1 clay from the general supply on this card. You must immediately exchange 4 clay on this card for 1 wild boar, held by this card.

name: Pipe Smoker
description: At the start of each harvest, if you have at least 1 grain field, you get 2 wood.

name: Lumber Mill
description: Every improvement costs you 1 wood less.

name: Forest Well
description: Place 1 food on each remaining round space, up to the amount of wood in your supply. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Beneficiary
description: If this is your 3rd occupation, you can immediately play another occupation for an occupation cost of 1 food and/or play 1 minor improvement by paying its cost.

name: Junior Artist
description: Each time after you use the "Day Laborer" action space, you can pay 1 food to use an unoccupied "Traveling Players" or "Lessons" action space with the same person.

name: Supply Boat
description: Each time after you use the "Fishing" accumulation space, you can choose to buy 1 grain for 1 food, or 1 vegetable for 3 food.

name: Mole Plow
description: Each time you use the "Farmland" or "Cultivation" action space, you can plow 1 additional field.

name: Sundial
description: At the end of the work phases in rounds 7 and 9, you can take a "Sow" action without placing a person.

name: Wood Expert
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 wood. Each improvement costs you up to 2 wood less, if you pay 1 food instead.

name: Land Register
description: During scoring, if your farm has no unused spaces, you get 2 bonus points.

name: Stable Tree
description: Each time you build 1 or more stables on your turn, place 1 wood on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the wood.

name: Firewood
description: In the returning home phase of each round, place 1 wood on this card. Each time before you build a Fireplace, Cooking Hearth, or oven, move up to 4 wood from this card to your supply.

name: Storeroom
description: During scoring, you get 1/2 bonus point for each pair of grain plus vegetable you have (considering all crops in your supply and fields), rounded up.

name: Upholstery
description: Each time you build or play an improvement after this one, you can place 1 reed on this card, irretrievably, to get 1 bonus point, up to the number of rooms in your house.

name: Animal Catcher
description: Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, instead of 2 food, you can get 3 different animals from the general supply. If you do, you must pay 1 food each harvest left to play.

name: Priest
description: When you play this card, if you live in a clay house with exactly 2 rooms, you immediately get 3 clay, 2 reed, and 2 stone.

name: Game Catcher
description: When you play this card, pay 1 food for each remaining harvest to immediately get 1 cattle and 1 wild boar.

name: Estate Worker
description: Place 1 wood, 1 clay, 1 reed, and 1 stone in this order on the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective building resource.

name: Seed Pellets
description: Each time before you take an unconditional "Sow" action, you get 1 grain.

name: Wild Greens
description: Each time you sow, you get 1 food for every different type of good that you sow.

name: Store of Experience
description: If you have 0-4/5/6/7 occupations left in hand, you immediately get 1 stone/reed/clay/wood.

name: Den Builder
description: When you live in a clay or stone house, you can pay 1 grain and 2 food. If you do, for the rest of the game, this card provides room for exactly one person.

name: Bunk Beds
description: Once you have 4 rooms, your house can hold 5 people.

name: Buyer
description: Each time another player uses a reed, stone, sheep, or wild boar accumulation space, you can pay them 1 food to get 1 good of the respective type from the general supply.

name: Clay Warden
description: Each time another player uses the "Hollow" accumulation space, you get 1 clay. In a 3-/4-player game, you also get 1 additional clay/food.

name: Pond Hut
description: Place 1 food on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Studio
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 wood/clay/stone into 2/2/3 food.

name: Sheep Rug

name: Hammer Crusher
description: Immediately before you renovate to stone, you get 2 clay and 1 reed and you can take a "Build Rooms" action.

name: Profiteering
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 food. Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, you can exchange 1 building resource for another building resource.

name: Artisan District
description: During scoring, you get 2/5/8 bonus points for having 3/4/5 major improvements from the bottom row of the supply board.

name: Kettle
description: At any time, you can exchange 1/3/5 grain for 3/4/5 food and 0/1/2 bonus points.

name: Raised Bed
description: At the start of each harvest, you get 4 food.

name: Straw-Thatched Roof
description: You no longer need reed to renovate or build a room.

name: Double-Turn Plow
description: When you play this card, you can immediately plow up to 2 fields.

name: Bricklayer
description: Each improvement and each renovation cost you 1 clay less. Each room costs you 2 clay less.

name: Conservator
description: You can renovate your wooden house directly to stone without renovating it to clay first.

name: Pole Barns
description: You can immediately build up to 3 stables at no cost.

name: Bottles
description: For each person you have, you must pay an additional 1 clay and 1 food to play this card.

name: Ebonist
description: Each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 wood into 1 food and 1 grain.

name: Roman Pot
description: Place 4 food from the general supply on this card. At the start of each work phase, if you are the last player in turn order, move 1 food from this card to your supply.

name: Seaweed Fertilizer
description: Each time after you take an unconditional "Sow" action, you get 1 grain from the general supply. From round 11 on, you can get 1 vegetable instead.

name: Fodder Beets
description: Place 1 food on each remaining odd-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Retraining
description: At the end of each turn in which you renovate, you can exchange your Joinery for the Pottery or your Pottery for the Basketmaker's Workshop.

name: Diligent Farmer
description: When you play this card, if you would score the maximum 4 points in 3 scoring categories (including fenced stables), you can extend your house by 1 room at no cost.

name: Bed in the Grain Field
description: At the start of the next harvest, you get a "Family Growth" action if you have room for the newborn.

name: Roof Ballaster
description: When you play this card, you can immediately pay 1 food to get 1 stone for each room you have.

name: Rod Collection
description: Each time you use "Fishing", you can place up to 2 wood on this card, irretrievably. During scoring, each such wood is worth 1 bonus point, except the 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th.

name: Flail
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 food. Each time you use the "Farmland" or "Cultivation" action space, you can also take a "Bake Bread" action.

name: Market Stall
description: After the field phase of each harvest, you can exchange 1 grain plus 1 fence (both from your supply) for 5 food.

name: Truffle Slicer
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, if you have at least 1 wild boar, you can pay 1 food for 1 bonus point.

name: Village Peasant
description: At the start of scoring, you get a number of vegetables equal to the smallest of the numbers of major improvements, minor improvements, and occupations you have.

name: Strawberry Patch
description: Place 1 food on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Claypipe
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if you gained at least 7 building resources in the preceding work phase, you get 2 food.

name: Work Permit
description: Add 1 to the current round for each building resource you have and place 1 person from your supply on the corresponding round space. In that round, you can use the person.
prerequisites: At Least 1 Building Resource in Your Supply

name: Clay Deliveryman
description: Place 1 clay on each remaining space for rounds 6 to 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the clay.

name: Potato Digger
description: When you play this card, if you have at least 2/4/5 unplanted field tiles, you immediately get 1/2/3 vegetables.

name: Large Pottery
description: At any time: Clay ‚Üí 2 Food Scoring: 3/5/6/7 Clay ‚Üí 1/2/3/4 bonus points

name: Stable
description: Immediately build 1 stable. (The stable costs you nothing, but you must pay the cost shown on this card.)

name: Seasonal Worker
description: Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, you get 1 additional grain. From round 6 on, you can choose to get 1 vegetable instead.

name: Scythe
description: During the field phase of each harvest, you can select exactly one of your fields and harvest all the goods planted in it.

name: Shepherd's Crook
description: Each time you fence a new pasture covering at least 4 farmyard spaces, you immediately get 2 sheep on this pasture.

name: Fruit Ladder
description: Place 1 food on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Small Basket
description: Each time you use the "Reed Bank" accumulation space, you can pay 1 reed to get 1 vegetable. If you do in a game with 4+ players, place that 1 reed on the accumulation space.

name: Zigzag Harrow
description: You can immediately plow 1 field such that it completes a "zigzag" pattern.

description: At the start of the field phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1 grain field, 1 vegetable field, and 1 empty field, you get 3 food.

name: Water Worker
description: Each time after you use the "Fishing" accumulation space or one of the three orthogonally adjacent actions spaces, you get 1 additional reed.

name: Straw Hat
description: At the end of the work phases of rounds 3 and 6, you can move your person from the "Farmland" action space to an unoccupied action space and take that action, or get 1 food.

name: Wood Cutter
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get 1 additional wood.

name: Mayor Candidate
description: You immediately get 2 wood and 2 stone. During scoring, you get 1 negative point for each wood and each stone in your supply. You can no longer discard wood or stone.

name: Master Builder
description: Once your house has at least 5 rooms, at any time, but only once this game, you can add another room at no cost.

name: Night Loot
description: Immediately remove 2 different building resources total from accumulation spaces and place them in your supply.

name: Stew
description: Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, also place 1 food on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Half-Timbered House
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each stone room you have. You can only use one card to get bonus points for your stone house.

name: Junk Room
description: Each time after you build an improvement, including this one, you get 1 food.

name: Established Person
description: If your house has exactly 2 rooms, immediately renovate it without paying any building resources. If you do, you can immediately afterward take a "Build Fences" action.

name: Fellow Grazer
description: During scoring, you get 2 bonus points of reach pasture you have covering at least 3 farmyard spaces.

name: Fern Seeds
description: You get 2 food and 1 grain, which you must sow immediately.

name: Small Greenhouse
description: Add 4 and 7 to the current round and place 1 vegetable on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you can buy the vegetable for 1 food.

name: Child's Toy
description: During the feeding phase of each harvest, your newborns require 2 food (instead of 1).

name: Trap Builder
description: Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, place 1 food, 1 food, and 1 wild boar on the next 3 round spaces, respectively. At the start of these rounds, you get the good.

name: Remodeling
description: You immediately get 1 clay for each clay room and for each major improvement you have.

name: Boar Spear
description: Each time you get wild boar outside of the breeding phase of a harvest, you can immediately turn them into 4 food each.

name: Dentist
description: At the start of each harvest, you can place 1 wood from your supply on this card, irretrievably. In each feeding phase, you get 1 food for each wood on this card.

name: Paintbrush
description: Each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 clay for your choice of 2 food or 1 bonus point.

name: Baking Course
description: At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you can take a "Bake Bread" action. "Bake Bread" action: Grain ‚Üí 2 Food

name: Harpooner
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" accumulation space you can also pay 1 wood to get 1 food for each person you have, and 1 reed
