description: At the end of each work phase, you can place 1 food on this card, irretrievably. At any time, you can discard 6 food from this to build a major improvement at no cost.

name: Foreign Aid
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 6 food. You may no longer use the action spaces of rounds 12 to 14.

name: Conjurer
description: Each time you use the "traveling Players" accumulation space, you get an additional 1 wood and 1 grain.

name: Farm Store
description: After the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 food for 2 different building resources of your choice or 1 vegetable.

name: Lumber Pile
description: When you play this card, you can immediately return up to 3 stables from your farmyard board to your supply and get 3 wood for each.

name: Tutor
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each occupation played after this one.

name: Upscale Lifestyle
description: You immediately get 5 clay and a "Renovation" action. If you take the action, you must pay the renovation cost.

name: Patroness
description: Each time after you play an occupation after this one, you get 1 building resource of your choice.

name: Sack Cart
description: Place 1 grain each on the remaining spaces for rounds 5, 8, 11, and 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the grain.

name: Organic Farmer
description: During the scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each pasture containing at least 1 animal while having unused capacity for at least three more animals.

name: Collier
description: Each time after you use the "Clay Pit" or "Hollow" accumulation space, you get 1 wood. On "Clay Pit" you also get 1 additional reed.

name: Stone Weir
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" accumulation space, if there are 0/1/2/3 food on the space, you get an additional 4/3/2/1 food from the general supply.

name: Syrup Tap
description: Each time you get at least 1 wood from an action space, place 1 food on the next round space. At the start of that round, you get the food.

name: Horse-Drawn Boat
description: Alternate placing 1 food and 1 sheep on each remaining round space, starting with food. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Debt Security
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each major improvement you have, up to the number of your unused farmyard spaces.

name: Stock Protector
description: Each time before you use the "Fencing" action space, you get 2 wood. Immediately after that "Fencing" action, you can place another person.

name: Chicken Coop
description: Place 1 food on each of the next 8 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Stockman
description: When you build your 2nd/3rd/4th stable, you immediately get 1 cattle/wild boar/sheep, even if built on the same turn (but not retroactively).

name: Farmers Market
description: You immediately get 1 vegetable.

name: Fatstock Stretcher
description: Each time you turn a sheep or wild boar into food using a baking improvement, you get 1 additional food.

name: Chairman
description: Each time another player uses the "Meeting Place" action space, both they and you get 1 food (before taking the actions). If you use it, you get 1 food.

name: Swimming Class
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if you return a person from the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get 2 bonus points for each newborn that you return home.

name: Chophouse
description: Each time you use the "Grain/Vegetable Seed" action space, place 1 food on each of the next 3/2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Museum Caretaker
description: At the start of each work phase, if you have at least 1 wood, 1 clay, 1 reed, 1 stone, 1 grain, and 1 vegetable in your supply, you get 1 bonus point.

name: Simple Oven
description: "Bake Bread" action: [1 grain -(1√ó)-> 3 food] When you play this card, you can immediately take a "Bake Bread" action.

name: Prophet
description: When you play this card, immediately take a "Renovation" action. Afterward, you can take a "Build Fences" action. (Both actions require their usual cost.)

name: Ambition
description: Each time you get a "Minor Improvement" action on an action space, you can build a major improvement instead of playing a minor one.

name: Potato Harvester
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 3 food. For each vegetable you get from your fields during the field phase of the harvest, you get 1 additional food.

name: Stone Company
description: Immediately after each time you use a "Quarry" accumulation space, you get a "Major or Minor Improvement" action during which you must spend at least 1 stone.

name: Carpenter
description: Every new room only costs you 3 of the appropriate building resource and 2 reed (e.g. if you live in a wooden house, 3 wood and 2 reed).

name: Seducer
description: When you play this card in round 5 or later, you can immediately pay 1 stone, 1 grain, 1 vegetable, and 1 sheep to take a "Family Growth Even without Room" action.

name: Seed Trader
description: Place 2 grain and 2 vegetables on this card. You can buy them at any time. Each grain costs 2 food; each vegetable costs 3 food.

name: Mineral Feeder
description: At the start of each round that does not end with a harvest, if you have at least 1 sheep in a pasture, you get 1 grain.

name: Beer Tap
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 food. In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can turn 2/3/4 grain into 3/6/9 food.

name: Archway
description: This card is an action space for all. A player who uses it immediately gets 1 food. Immediately before the returning home phase, they can use an unoccupied action space with the person from this card.

name: Midwife
description: Each time another player uses the first person they place in a round to take a "Family Growth" action, you get 1 grain from the general supply.

name: Animal Bedding
description: You can keep 1 additional animal in each of your unfenced stables, and 2 additional animals in each pasture with stable.

name: Scholar
description: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 food, or a minor improvement (by paying its cost).

name: Scythe Worker
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 grain. In the field phase of each harvest, you can harvest 1 additional grain from each of your grain fields.

name: Carter
description: Next round, each time you use a building resource accumulation space, you also get 1 food for each building resource that you take from the space.

name: Town Hall
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, if you live in a clay or stone house, you get 1 or 2 food, respectively.

name: Delivery Nurse
description: Once this game, if you have all types of animals, you can turn a "Family Growth" action into a "Family Growth Even without Room" action.

name: Sheep Well
description: Place 1 food on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of sheep you have. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Forest Lake Hut
description: Each time you use the "Fishing"/"Forest" accumulation space, you also get 1 wood/food.

name: Threshing Board
description: Each time you use the "Farmland" or "Cultivation" action space, you get an additional "Bake Bread" action.

name: Thunderbolt
description: Immediately remove all grain from one of your fields to the general supply. Gain 2 wood for each grain you just removed.

name: Stonecutter
description: Every improvement, room, and renovation costs you 1 stone less.

name: Shelter
description: You can immediately build a stable at no cost, but only if you place it in a pasture covering exactly 1 farmyard space.

name: Brushwood Collector
description: Each time you renovate or build a room, you can replace the required 1 or 2 reed with a total of 1 wood.

name: Wildlife Reserve
description: This card can hold up to 1 sheep, 1 wild boar, and 1 cattle.

name: Equipper
description: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can play a minor improvement.

name: Master Bricklayer
description: Each time you build a major improvement, reduce the stone cost by the number of rooms you have built onto you initial house.

name: Paper Maker
description: Immediately before playing each occupation after this one, you can pay 1 wood total to get 1 food for each occupation you have in front of you.

name: Portmonger
description: Each time you take 1/2/3+ food from a food accumulation space, you also get 1 vegetable/grain/reed.

name: Reseller
description: Once this game, immediately after playing or building an improvement, you can choose to get its printed cost from the general supply.

name: Bale of Straw
description: At the start of each harvest, if you have at least 3 grain fields (including field cards with planted grain), you get 2 food.

name: Storehouse Keeper
description: Each time you use the "resource Market" action space, you also get your choice of 1 clay or 1 grain.

name: Seed Seller
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 grain. Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you get 1 additional grain.

name: Rocky Terrain
description: Each time you plow a field (tile or card), you can also buy 1 stone for 1 food.

name: Thresher
description: Immediately before each time you use the "Grain Utilization", "Farmland", or "Cultivation" action space, you can buy 1 grain for 1 food.

name: Bread Paddle
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 food. For each occupation you play, you get an additional "Bake Bread" action.

name: Thick Forest
description: Place 1 wood on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the wood.

name: Animal Dealer
description: Each time you use the "Sheep Market", "Pig Market", "or "Cattle Market" accumulation space, you can buy 1 additional animal of the respective type for 1 food.

name: Housebook Master
description: After playing this card, if you renovate to stone in round 13/12/11 or before, you immediately get 1/2/3 food and 1/2/3 bonus points.

name: Housemaster
description: During scoring, total the point values of your major improvements. The smallest value counts double. If the total is at least 5/7/9/11, you get 1/2/3/4 bonus points.

name: Moonshine
description: Randomly select an occupation in your hand. Either play it for an occupation cost of 2 food, or give it to the player to your left.

name: Cheese Fondue
description: Each time you bake at least 1 grain into bread, you get 1 additional food if you have at least 1 sheep and 1 additional food if you have at least 1 cattle.

name: Stork's Nest
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have more rooms than people, you can pay 1 food to take a "Family Growth" action.

name: Calcium Fertilizers
description: Each time you use a "Quarry" accumulation space, add 1 additional good of the respective type to each of your planted fields growing a single type of crop.

name: Final Scenario
description: Place the action space card for round 14 face up in front of you. Only you can use it until it is placed on the game board.

name: Recycled Brick
description: Each time any player (including you) renovates to stone, you get 1 clay for each newly renovated room.

name: Firewood Collector
description: Each time you use the "Farmland", "Grain Seeds", Grain Utilization", or "Cultivation" action space, at the end of that turn, you get 1 wood.

name: Fish Farmer
description: Each time there is 1/2/3+ food on the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get an additional 2 food on the "Reed Bank"/ "Clay Pit"/ "Forest" accumulation spaces.

name: Master Tanner
description: For each wild boar or cattle you turn into food, you can place 1 of that food on this card. Once its food equals your number of rooms, this card provides room for 1 person.

name: Casual Worker
description: Each time another player uses a "Quarry" accumulation space, you can choose to get 1 food or build a stable without paying wood.

name: Clay Puncher
description: When you play this card and each time after you use a "Lessons" action space or the "Clay Pit" accumulation space, you get 1 clay.

name: Stable Master
description: When you play this card, you can immediately build exactly 1 stable for 1 wood. Exactly one of your unfenced stables can hold up to 3 animals of one type.

name: Food Chest
description: If you play this card on the "Major Improvement" action space, you immediately get 4 food. Otherwise, you get only 2 food.

name: Animal Feeder
description: On the "Day Laborer" action space, you also get your choice of 1 sheep or 1 grain. Instead of that good, you can buy 1 wild boar for 1 food or 1 cattle for 2 food.

name: Steam Machine
description: Each work phase, if the last action space you use is an accumulation space, you can immediately afterward take a "Bake Bread" action.

name: Stone Cart
description: Place 1 stone on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the stone.

name: Handcart
description: Before each work phase, you can take 1 building resource from at most one wood/clay/reed/stone accumulation space containing at least 6/5/4/4 building resources of the same type.

name: Pastor
description: Once you are the only player to live in a house with only 2 rooms, you immediately get 3 wood, 2 clay, 1 reed, and 1 stone (only once).

name: Seed Researcher
description: Each time any people return from both the "Grain Seeds" and "Vegetable Seeds" action spaces, you get 2 food and you can play 1 occupation, without paying an occupation cost.

name: Fodder Planter
description: In the breeding phase of each harvest, for each newborn animal you get, you can sow crops in exactly 1 field.

name: Hunting Trophy
description: Improvements built on "House Redevelopment" cost you 1 building resource of your choice less. Fences built on "Farm Redevelopment" cost you a total of 3 wood less.

name: Comb and Cutter
description: Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, you get 1 additional food for each sheep on the "Sheep Market" accumulation space, up to a maximum of 4 additional food.

name: Spice Trader
description: If you play this card in round 4 or before, place 3 vegetables on the space for round 11. At the start of that round, you get the vegetables.

name: Reed Belt
description: Place 1 reed on each of the remaining space for rounds 5, 8, 10, and 12. At the start of these rounds, you get the reed.

name: Grain Bag
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you get 1 additional grain for each <BAKE> improvement you have.

name: Acorns Basket
description: Place 1 wild boar on each of the 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the wild boar.

name: Manger
description: During scoring, if your pastures cover at least 6/7/8/10 farm yard spaces, you get 1/2/3/4 bonus points.

name: Cottager
description: Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, you can also either build exactly 1 room or renovate your house. Either way, you have to pay the cost.

name: Pumpernickel
description: You immediately get 4 food.

name: Canoe
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get an additional 1 food and 1 reed.

name: Potter's Yard
description: Immediately place 1 clay on each unused space in your farmyard. Each time you turn a space into a used space, you get the clay and you can immediately exchange it for 2 food.

name: Fishing Net
description: Each time another player uses the "Fishing" accumulation space, they must first pay you 1 food. Then, in the returning home phase of that round, place 2 food on "Fishing".

name: Spin Doctor
description: Immediately after each time you use the "Traveling Players" accumulation space, you can place another person on an action space of your choice, regardless whether or not the action space is occupied.

name: Agricultural Labourer
description: Place 8 clay on this card. For each grain you obtain, you also get 1 clay from this card.

name: Consultant
description: When you play this card in a 1-/2-/3-/4- player game, you immediately get 2 grain/3 clay/2 reed/2 sheep.

name: Bellfounder
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have at least 1 clay, you can use this card to discard all of your clay and get your choice of 3 food or 1 bonus point.

name: Livestock Feeder
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 grain. Each grain in your supply can hold 1 animal of any type. (these animals count as accommodated on your farm.)

name: Shovel Bearer
description: Each time you use the "Clay Pit" or "Hollow" accumulation space, you also get a number of food equal to the amount of clay on the respective other accumulation space.

name: Fodder Chamber
description: During scoring in a game with 1/2/3/4+ players, you get 1 bonus point for every 7th/5th/4th/3rd animal on your farm.

name: Godmother
description: Each time you take a "Family Growth" action, you also get 1 vegetable.

name: Grange
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 food.
prerequisites: 6 Field Tiles and All Animal Types

name: Second Spouse
description: You can use the "Urgent Wish for Children" action space (from round 12-13) even if it is occupied by the first person another player placed.

name: Plumber
description: Each time after you use the "Major Improvement" action space, you can take a "renovation" action, paying 2 clay or 2 stone less for the renovation.

name: Mountain Plowman
description: Each time you plow at least 1 field, you get 1 sheep for each field that you just plowed.

name: Hide Farmer
description: During scoring, you can pay 1 food each for any number of unused farmyard spaces. If you do, you do not lose points for these spaces.

name: Forest Trader
description: Each time you use a wood or clay accumulation space, you can also buy exactly 1 building resource. Wood, clay, and reed cost 1 food each; stone costs 2 food.

name: Bee Statue
description: Pile (from bottom to top) 1 vegetable, 1 stone, 1 grain, 1 stone, 1 grain on this card. Each time you use the "Day Laborer" action space, you get the top good.

name: Wooden Shed
description: This card can only be played via a "Major Improvement" action. It provides room for one person. You may no longer renovate.

name: Renovation Company
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 3 clay. Immediately after, you can renovate without paying any building resources.
prerequisites: In Wooden House with Exactly 2 Rooms

name: Field Merchant
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 wood and 1 reed. Each time you decline a "Minor/Major Improvement" action, you get 1 food/vegetable instead.

name: Moral Crusader
description: Immediately before the start of each round, if there are goods on the remaining round space that are promised to you, you get 1 food.

name: Large Greenhouse
description: Add 4, 7, and 9 to the current round and place 1 vegetable on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the vegetable.

name: Schnapps Distillery
description: In each feeding phase, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 vegetable into 5 food. During scoring, you get 1 bonus point each for your 5th and 6th vegetable.

name: Bohemian
description: At the start of each returning home phase, if at least one "Lessons" action space is unoccupied, you get 1 food.

name: Pattern Maker
description: Each time another player renovates, you can exchange exactly 2 wood for 1 grain, 1 food, and 1 bonus point.

name: Crack Weeder
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 food. For each vegetable you take from a field in the field phase of a harvest, you also get 1 food.

name: Scullery
description: At the start of each round, if you live in a wooden house, you get 1 food.

name: Seed Servant
description: Each time after you use the "Grain Seeds" or "Vegetable Seeds" action space, you can take a "Bake bread" or "Sow" action, respectively.

name: Autumn Mother
description: Immediately before each harvest, if you have room in your house, you can take a "Family Growth" action for 3 food.

name: New Market
description: Each time you use an action space card on round spaces 8 to 11, you get 1 additional food.

name: Lodger
description: This card provides room for one person, but only until the returning home phase of round 9. If, by then, there is no room elsewhere for that person, remove it from play.

name: Hard Porcelain
description: At any time, you can exchange 2/3/4 clay for 1/2/3 stone.

name: Forest Owner
description: This card is an action space for all. If another player uses it, they get 3 wood and must give you 1 wood from the general supply. If you use it, you get 4 wood.

name: Elder
description: You can play this card at the start of the work phase of round 1 without placing a person. (This card has no effect other than counting as a played occupation.)

name: Patch Caregiver
description: When you play this card, you can choose to buy 1 grain for 1 food, or 1 vegetable for 3 food. This card is a field.

name: Bartering Hut
description: Up to two times: Immediately spend any 2/3/4 building resources for 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle from the general supply.

name: Milking Parlor
description: When you play this card, if you have at least 1/3/4 sheep, you immediately get 2/3/4 food. The same applies if you have at least 1/2/3 cattle.

name: Lasso
description: You can place exactly two people immediately after one another if at least one of them uses the "Sheep Market", "Pig Market", or "Cattle Market" accumulation space.

name: Lieutenant General
description: For each field tile that another player places next to an existing field tile, you get 1 food from the general supply. In round 14, you get 1 grain instead.

name: Lawn Fertilzer
description: Your pastures of size 1 can hold up to 3 animals of the same type. (With a stable, they can hold up to 6 animals of the same type.)

name: Automatic Water Trough
description: If you can accommodate the animal, you can immediately buy 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle for 0/1/2 food.

name: Garden Hoe
description: Each time you take an unconditional "Sow" action planting vegetables in at least 1 field, you get 1 clay and 1 stone.

name: Woodcraft
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, if immediately afterward you have at most 5 wood in your supply, you get 1 food.

name: Skimmer Plow
description: Each time you use the "Farmland" or "Cultivation" action space, you can plow 2 fields instead of 1. Each time you sow, you must place 1 fewer good on each field you sow.

name: Clay Kneader
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 wood and 2 clay. Each time after you use a "Grain Seeds" or "Vegetable Seeds" action space, you get 1 clay.

name: Muck Rake
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for exactly 1 unfenced stable holding exactly 1 sheep. The same applies to wild boar and cattle, if held in different unfenced stables.

name: Trout Pool
description: At the start of each work phase, if there are at least 3 food on the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get 1 food from the general supply.

name: Layabout
description: When you play this card, you must skip the next harvest. (You also do not have to feed your family that harvest.)

name: Herbal Garden
description: From now on, at least one of your pastures must contain no animals.

name: Hoof Caregiver
description: Immediately add 1 cattle from the general supply to the "Cattle Market" accumulation space. Afterward, you get 1 grain plus 1 food for each cattle on "Cattle Market".

name: Clay Plasterer
description: Renovating to clay only costs you exactly 1 clay and 1 reed. Each clay room only costs you 3 clay and 2 reed to build.

name: Market Crier
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you can get an additional 1 grain and 1 vegetable. If you do, each other player gets 1 grain from the general supply.

name: Feeding Dish
description: Each time you use an animal accumulation space while already having an animal of that type, you get 1 grain.

name: Renovation Materials
description: Immediately renovate to clay at no cost.

name: Bed Maker
description: Each time you add rooms to your house, you can also pay 1 wood and 1 grain to immediately get a "Family Growth with Room Only" action.

name: Baking Sheet
description: Each time you take a "Bake Bread" action, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 grain for 2 food and 1 bonus point.

name: Hook Knife
description: Once this game, when you have 9/8/7/6/5/5 sheep on your farm in a 1-/2-3-/4-/5-/6- player game, you immediately get 2 bonus points.

name: Wood Pile
description: You immediately get a number of wood equal to the number of people you have on accumulation spaces.

name: Kelp Gatherer
description: Each time another player uses the "Fishing" accumulation space, they get 1 additional food and you get 1 vegetable.

name: Field Cultivator
description: Pile 1 wood, 1 clay, 1 reed, 1 stone, 1 reed, 1 clay, and 1 wood on this card. Each time you harvest a field tile, you can also take the top good from the pile.

name: Studio Boat
description: Each time you use the "Traveling Players" accumulation space, you also get 1 bonus point. In games with 1-3 players, this card is considered "Traveling Players" (same effect as "Fishing").

name: Field Spade
description: Each time after you sow in at least 1 field, you get 1 stone.

name: Pottery Yard
description: During the scoring, if there are at least 2 orthogonally adjacent unused spaces in your farm, you get 2 bonus points. (You still get the negative points for those unused spaces.

name: Lumberjack
description: You immediately get 1 wood. Additionally, place 1 wood on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of fences you built. At the start of these rounds, you get the wood.

name: Puppeteer
description: Each time another player uses the "Traveling Players" accumulation space, you can pay them 1 food to immediately play an occupation without paying an occupation cost.

name: Changeover
description: At any time, if a field contains exactly 1 good as a result of a harvest, you can discard that good and immediately take a "Sow" action limited to that field.

name: Greengrocer
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you also get 1 vegetable.

name: Ropemaker
description: At the end of each harvest, you get 1 reed from the general supply.

name: Entrepreneur
description: At the start of each round, you can move 1 food to this card or discard 1 food from it. If you do either, you get 1 building resource of a type you currently do not have.

name: Schnapps Distiller
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 vegetable into 5 food.

name: Brick Hammer
description: Each time after you build an improvement costing at least 2 clay, you get 1 stone.

name: Pub Owner
description: Immediately, when you play this card, and at the end of each work phase, in which the "Forest", "Clay Pit", and "Reed Bank" accumulation spaces are all occupied, you get 1 grain.

name: Eternal Rye Cultivation
description: After each harvest in which you have 2 or 3+ grain in your supply, you get 1 food and 1 additional grain, respectively.

name: Hill Cultivator
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" or "Vegetable Seeds" action space, you also get 2 or 3 clay, respectively.

name: Smuggler
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange up to 2 goods as follows: [1 Wood => 1 Grain] or [1 Grain => 1 Stone]

name: Animal Driver
description: At the start of each harvest, if you have 1/2/3+ fenced stables, you get 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle.

name: Stone Clearing
description: Immediately place 1 stone on each of your empty fields. Harvest them during the next field phase. These fields are considered planted until then.

name: Baker
description: When you play this card and at the start of each feeding phase, you can take a "Bake Bread" action.

name: Drift-Net Boat
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get an additional 2 food.

name: Soil Scientist
description: Each time after you use a clay/stone accumulation space, you can place 1 stone/2 clay from your supply on the space to get 2 grain/1 vegetable, respectively.

name: Forestry Studies
description: Each time after you use the "Forest" accumulation space, you can return 2 wood to that space to play 1occupation without paying an occupation costs.

name: Heirloom
description: This card has no additional effect.

name: Farm Building
description: Each time you build a major improvement, place 1 food on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Market Stall
description: After the field phase of each harvest, you can exchange 1 grain plus 1 fence (both from your supply) for 5 food.

name: Party Organizer
description: As soon as the next player but you gains their 5th person, you immediately get 8 food (not retroactively). During scoring, if only you have 5 people, you get 3 bonus points.

name: Lantern House
description: During scoring, you get 1 negative point for each card left in your hand. You cannot discard cards from your hand unplayed. If you already have, you cannot play this card.

name: Corn Scoop
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you get 1 additional grain.

name: Clay Firer
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 clay. At any time, you can turn clay into stone: you get 1 stone for 2 clay, and 2 stone for 3 clay.

name: Asparagus Gift
description: Each time you build a number of fences equal to or great than the current round, you immediately get 1 vegetable.

name: Furrows
description: You can immediately sow in exactly 1 field.

name: Journeyman Bricklayer
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 stone. Each time another player renovates to stone or builds a stone room, you get 1 stone.

name: Fire Protection Pond
description: Once you no longer live in a wooden house, place 1 food on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Roastmaster
description: Each time you use the "Traveling Players" or "Fishing" accumulation spaces, you can move exactly 1 food from that space to the other to get 1 cattle.

name: Dwelling Plan
description: You can immediately take a "Renovation" action.

name: Stone Tongs
description: Each time you use a stone accumulation space, you get 1 additional stone.

name: German Heath Keeper
description: Each time any player (including you) uses the "Pig Market" accumulation space, you get 1 sheep from the general supply.

name: Vegetable Slicer
description: Each time you upgrade a Fireplace to a Cooking Hearth, you immediately get 2 wood and 1 vegetable (not retroactively).

name: Clearing Spade
description: At any time, you can move 1 crop from a planted field containing at least 2 crops to an empty field.

name: Lutenist
description: Each time another player uses the "Traveling Players" accumulation space, you get 1 food and 1 wood. Immediately after, you can buy exactly 1 vegetable for 2 food.

name: Manservant
description: Once you live in a stone house, place 3 food on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Oyster Eater
description: Each time the "Fishing" accumulation space is used, you get 1 bonus point and must skip placing your next person that round. (You can place the person on a later turn.)

name: Shifting Cultivator
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can also play 3 food to plow 1 field.

name: Straw Manure
description: Before the field phase of each harvest, you can pay 1 grain from your supply to add 1 vegetable to each of up to 2 vegetable fields.

name: Tree Cutter
description: Each time you use an accumulation space providing at least 3 goods of the same type except wood, you get an additional 1 wood. (Food is also considered a good.)

name: Fisherman's Friend
description: At the start of each round, if there is more food on the "Traveling Players" than on the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get the difference from the general supply.

name: Herring Pot
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" accumulation space, place 1 food on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Domestician Expert
description: You can keep 2 sheep on the border between each pair of orthogonally adjacent rooms.

name: Grain Sieve
description: In the field phase of each harvest, if you harvest at least 2 grain, you get 1 additional grain from the general supply.

name: Game Trade
description: You immediately get 1 wild boar and 1 cattle. (effectively, you are exchanging 2 sheep for 1 wild boar and 1 cattle.)

name: District Manager
description: At the end of each work phase, if you used both the "Forest" and "Grove" accumulation spaces, you get 5 food.

name: Tax Collector
description: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you get your choice of 2 wood, 2 clay, 1 reed, or 1 stone.

name: Asparagus Knife
description: In the returning home phase of rounds 8, 10, and 12, you can take 1 vegetable from exactly 1 vegetable field. You can immediately exchange it for 3 food and 1 bonus point.

name: Resource Recycler
description: Each time another player renovates to stone, if you live in a clay house, you can pay 2 food to build a clay room at no additional cost.

name: Braid Maker
description: Each harvest, you can use this card to exchange 1 reed for 2 food. You can build the Basket Maker's Workshop for 1 reed and 1 stone even when taking a "Minor Impr." action.

name: Master Fencer
description: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can pay 2 or 3 wood to build up to 3 or 4 fences, respectively.

name: Lazy Sowman
description: Each time you decline an unconditional "Sow" action on your turn, you can immediately place another person on an action space of your choice (even if it is occupied).

name: Stable Architect
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each unfenced stable in your farmyard.

name: Swagman
description: Immediately after each time you use the "Farm Expansion" or "Grain Seeds" action space, you can use the respective other space with the same person (even if it is occupied).

name: Roof Examiner
description: When you play this card, if you have 1/2/3/4 major improvements, you immediately get 2/3/4/5 reed.

name: Churchyard
description: Place 2 food on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the food. (*Occupations and Improvements)

name: Gardener's Knife
description: You immediately get 1 food for each grain field you have and 1 grain for each vegetable field you have.

name: Stone Buyer
description: When you play this card, you can immediately buy exactly 2 stone for 1 food. From the next round on, one per round, you can buy 1 stone for 2 food.

name: Sower
description: Each time you build a major improvement, place 1 reed from the general supply on that card. At any time, you can move the reed to your supply or exchange it for a "Sow" action.

name: Brewing Water
description: Each time you use the "Fishing" accumulation space, you can pay 1 grain to place 1 food on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Home Brewer
description: After the field phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 grain into your choice of 3 food or 1 bonus point.

name: Civic Facade
description: Before the start of each round, if you have more occupations than improvements in your hand, you get 1 food.

name: Potato Planter
description: At the end of each work phase in which you occupy the "Clay Pit" or "Reed Bank" accumulation space while the respective other is unoccupied, you get 1 vegetable.

name: Chief Forester
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you also get a "Sow" action for exactly 1 field.

name: Mandoline
description: Once per round, you can pay 1 vegetable to get 1 bonus point. If you do, place 1 food on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Young Animal Market
description: You immediately get 1 cattle. (Effectively, you are exchanging 1 sheep for 1 cattle.)

name: Sheep Keeper
description: You can only play this card if you have less than 7 sheep. Once this game, when you have 7 sheep on your farm, you immediately get 3 bonus points and 2 food.

name: Millwright
description: You immediately get 1 grain. Each time you build fences, stables, and rooms, or renovate your house, you can replace up to 2 building resources of any type with 1 grain each.

name: Beer Stein
description: Each time you take a "Bake Bread" action, you can use this card once to turn 1 grain into 2 food and 1 bonus point.

name: Tinsmith Master
description: You can hold 1 additional animal in each pasture without a stable. Each time you sow in a field, you can place 1 additional crop of the respective type in that field.

name: Emergency Seller
description:
When you play this card, you can immediately turn as many building resources into food as you have people:
[wood]/[clay] -> 2 [food]
[reed]/[stone] -> 3 [food]

name: Tea Time
description: Immediately return your person on the "Grain Utilization" action space home; you can place it again later this round.

name: Margrave
description: Once you live in a stone house, you get 2 food each time any player (including you) renovates and, during scoring, 1 bonus point for each wood house and clay house.

name: Rustic
description: For each clay room you build, you get 2 food and 1 bonus point. (this does not apply to stone rooms and renovated wood rooms.)

name: Farmyard Manure
description: Each time you build 1 or more stables in one turn, you place 1 food on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Miller
description: You can immediately build a <BAKE> improvement by paying its cost. Each time another player uses the "Grain Seeds" action space, you can take a ‚ÄúBake Bread‚Äù action.

name: Reader
description: As soon as you have 6 occupations in front of you (including this one), this cards provides room for one person. In the draft variant, you need 7 occupations to play this.

name: Parvenu
description: If you play this card in round 7 or before, immediately double the amount of clay or reed in your supply.

name: Tasting
description: Each time you use a "Lessons" action space, before paying the occupation cost, you can exchange 1 grain for 4 food.

name: Toolbox
description: In the work phase, after each turn in which you build at least 1 room, stable, or fence, you can build the "Joinery", "pottery", or Basketmaker's Workshop" major improvement.

name: Old Miser
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, each of your people requires 1 less food. During scoring, your people are worth 2 points each instead of 3.

name: Green Grocer
description: At the start of each round, you can make exactly one of the following exchanges: 1 Cattle ‚Üí 1 Vegetable; 1 Vegetable ‚Üí 1 Cattle; 2 Sheep ‚Üí 1 Vegetable; 1 Vegetable ‚Üí 2 Sheep; 2 Food ‚Üí 1 Grain; 1 Grain ‚Üí 2 Food

name: Wood Harvester
description: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 wood/1 food for each wood accumulation space with exactly 2 wood/at least 3 wood.

name: Huntsman's Hat
description: For each new wild boar you get from the effect of an action space, you also get 1 food.

name: Recount
description: You immediately get 1 building resource of each type of which you have 4 or more resources in your supply already.

name: Forest Inn
description: This is an action space for all. A player who uses it can exchange 5/7/9 wood for 8 wood and 2/4/7 food. When another player uses it, they must first pay you 1 food.

name: Salter
description: At any time, you can pay 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle from you farm. If you do, place 1 food on each of the next 3/5/7 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Petrified Wood
description: Immediately exchange up to 3 wood for 1 stone each.

name: Pen Builder
description: At any time, you can place wood from your supply on this card, irretrievably. You can keep twice as many animals of any type on this card as there is wood on it.

name: Woolgrower
description: This card can hold a number of sheep equal to the number of completed feeding phases.

name: Stablehand
description: Each time you build at least 1 fence, you can also build a stable without paying wood for the stable.

name: Uncaring Parents
description: At the end of each harvest, if you live in a stone house, you get 1 bonus point.

name: Milking Place
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you get 1 food. You can no longer hold animals in your house (not even via another card).

name: Drinking Trough
description: Each of your pastures (with or without a stable) can hold up to 2 more animals.

name: Potato Ridger
description: Each time after you harvest 1+ vegetables, if you then have 3+ vegetables in your supply, you can turn exactly 1 vegetable into 6 food. With 4+ vegetables, you must do so.

name: Hollow Warden
description: When you play this card, you immediately get a "Major Improvement" action to build a Fireplace. Each time you use the "Hollow" accumulation space, you also get 1 food.

name: Forest School
description: You can consider the "Lessons" action spaces not occupied. You can replace each food that an occupation costs with wood.

name: Blighter
description: When you play this, you get 1 bonus point for each complete stage left to play. You may not play any more occupations.

name: Petting Zoo
description: As long as you have a pasture orthogonally adjacent to your house, you can keep animals of any type on this card, up to the number of rooms in your house.

name: Rock Beater
description: You can use an action space providing both stone and a different building resource even if it is occupied by another player. Stone rooms cost you 2 stone less.

name: Angler
description: Each time after you use the "Fishing" Accumulation space while there are at most 2 food on that space, you get a "Major or Minor Improvement" action.

name: Stone Custodian
description: At the end of each work phase, you get 1 food for each stone accumulation space with stone on it.

name: Emissary
description: At any time, you can place a good from your supply on this card to get 1 stone. You must place different goods on this card. (Food is also considered a good.)

name: Nutrition Expert
description: At the start of each round, you can exchange a set comprised of 1 animal of any type, 1 grain, and 1 vegetable for 5 food and 2 bonus points.

name: Iron Hoe
description: At the end of each work phase, if you occupy both the "Grain Seeds" and "Vegetable Seeds" action spaces, you can plow 1 field.

name: Pasture Master
description: Each time you renovate, you get 2 food and 1 additional animal of the respective type in each of your pastures with stable.

name: Forest Guardian
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 wood. Each time before another player takes at least 5 wood from an accumulation space, they must first pay you 1 food.

name: Stable Yard
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 food for each completed round left to play. At any time, you can exchange 1 sheep plus 1 wild boar for 1 cattle.

name: Flax Farmer
description: Each time you use the "Reed Bank" accumulation space, you also get 1 grain. Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you also get 1 reed.

name: Pigswill
description: Each time you use the "Fencing" action space, you also get 1 wild boar.

name: Sheep Agent
description: You can keep 1 sheep on each occupation card in front of you (including this one), unless it is already able to hold animals.

name: Feedyard
description: This card can hold 1 animal for each pasture you have, even different types. After the breeding phase of each harvest, you get 1 food for each unused spot on this card.

name: Misanthropy
description: During scoring, if you have exactly 4/3/2 people, you get 2/3/5 bonus points.

name: Transactor
description: Immediately before the final harvest at the end of round 14, you can take all the building resources that are left on the entire game board.

name: Pitchfork
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, if the "Farmland" action space is occupied you also get 3 food.

name: Freemason
description: As long as you live in a clay/stone house with exactly 2 rooms, at the start of each work phase, you get 2 clay/stone.

name: Stone Carver
description: Each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 stone into 3 food.

name: Groom
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 wood. Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 wood.

name: Ale-Benches
description: In the returning home phase of each round, you can pay exactly 1 grain from your supply to get 1 bonus point. If you do, each other player gets 1 food.

name: Timber Shingle Maker
description: When you renovate to stone, you can place up to 1 wood from your supply in each of your rooms. During scoring, each such wood is worth 1 bonus point.

name: Pig Breeder
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 wild boar. Your wild boar breed at the end of round 12 (if there is room for the new wild boar).

name: Plant Fertilizer
description: In each field with exactly 1 good, you can immediately place 1 additional good of the same type.

name: Geologist
description: Each time you use the "Forest" or "Reed Bank" accumulation space, you also get 1 clay. In games with 3 or more players, this also applies to the "Clay Pit".

name: Lumber Virtuoso
description: Each harvest in which you have at least 5 wood in your supply, you can discard down to 5 wood to take a "Build Stables" or "Build Wood Rooms" action by paying the usual costs.

name: Gritter
description: At the end of each action in which you sow vegetables in a field, you get 1 food for each vegetable field you have (including the new ones).

name: Beer Tent Operator
description: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn 1 wood plus 1 grain into 1 bonus point and 2 food.

name: Sculptor
description: Each time you use a clay accumulation space, you also get 1 food. Each time you use a stone accumulation space, you also get 1 grain.

name: Pellet Press
description: Once per round, you can pay 1 reed. If you do, place 1 food on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Gypsy's Crock
description: Each time you use a cooking improvement to turn 2 goods into food at the same time, you get 1 additional food.

name: Storage Barn
description: If you have the Well, Joinery, Pottery, and/or Basketmaker's Workshop, you immediately get 1 stone, 1 wood, 1 clay, and/or 1 reed, respectively.

name: Cowherd
description: Each time you use the "Cattle Market" accumulation space (introduced in round 10 or 11), you get 1 additional cattle.

name: Potters Market
description: At any time, you can pay 4 clay and 2 food. If you do, place 1 vegetable on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the vegetable.

name: Land Surveyor
description: In the field phase of each harvest, if you have at least 2/4/6/7 fields, you get 1/2/3/4 food.

name: Mantlepiece
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 bonus point for each complete round left to play. You may no longer renovate your house.

name: Whale Oil
description: Each time you use "Fishing", place 1 food from the general supply on this card. Each time before you play an occupation, you get food equal to the amount on this card.

name: Truffle Searcher
description: This card can hold a number of wild boar equal to the number of completed feeding phases.

name: Case Builder
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 good of each of the following types, If you have at least 2 of that good in your supply already, food, grain, vegetable, reed, wood.

name: Oven Firing Boy
description: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get an additional "Bake Bread" action.

name: Seatmate
description: You can use the action space on round space 13 even if it is occupied by one or more people of the players to your immediate left and right.

name: Renovation Preparer
description: For each new wood/clay room you build, you get 2 clay/2 stone.

name: Almsbag
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 grain for every 2 completed rounds.

name: Outrider
description: Each time before you use the action space on the most recently revealed action space card (after it has been placed on the round space), you get 1 grain.

name: Clay Embankment
description: You immediately get 1 clay for every 2 clay you already have in your supply.

name: Cube Cutter
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 wood. In the field phase of each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 wood and 1 food for 1 bonus point.

name: Cattle Feeder
description: Each time you use the "Grain Seeds" action space, you can also buy 1 cattle for 1 food.

name: Grain Thief
description: Each time you would harvest a grain field, you can leave the grain on the field and take 1 grain from the general supply instead.

name: Soldier
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each stone-wood pair in your supply. You cannot score additional points for the resources scored with this card.

name: Building Expert
description: Each time you use the "Resource Market" action space with the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th person you place, you also get 1 wood/clay/reed/stone/stone.

name: Storehouse Steward
description: Each time you take exactly 2/3/4/5 food from a food accumulation space, you also get 1 stone/reed/clay/wood. (If you take 6 or more food, you do not get a bonus good).

name: Digging Spade
description: Each time you use a clay accumulation space, you also get a number of food equal to the number of wild boar in your farmyard.

name: Blade Shears
description: You immediately get your choice of 3 food or 1 food for each sheep you have. (Keep the sheep.)

name: Mushroom Collector
description: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can exchange 1 wood for 2 food. If you do, place the wood on the accumulation space.

name: Mineralogist
description: Each time you use a clay/stone accumulation space, you also get 1 of the other good, stone/clay.

name: Recluse
description: As long as you have no minor improvements in front of you, you get 1 food at the start of each round and 1 wood at the start of each harvest.

name: Early Cattle
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 cattle.

name: Animal Tamer's Apprentice
description: At the start of each round, you get 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle for each unoccupied wood/clay/stone room in your house.

name: Livestock Expert
description: If you play this card in round 11 or before, choose an animal type: You immediately get a number of animals of that type equal to the number you already have on your farm.

name: Prodigy
description: If this is your 1st occupation, you immediately get 1 bonus point for each improvement you have. (This will not apply to improvements played after this card.)

name: Stable Manure
description: In the field phase of each harvest, you can harvest 1 additional good from a number of fields equal to the number of unfenced stables you have.

name: Barley Mill
description: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 food for each grain field that you harvest.

name: Field Clay
description: You immediately get 1 clay for each planted field you have.

name: Usufructuary
description: When you play this card as your first occupation, you immediately get 1 food for every other occupation in play (by any player), up to a maximum of 7 food.

name: Earthenware Potter
description: If you play this card in round 4 or before, after the final harvest, you get 1 bonus point for each person for which you then pay 1 clay.

name: Outskirts Director
description: Each time you use the "Grove" or "Hollow" accumulation space, you can place 2 reed from the general supply on the other space. If you do, you can immediately place another person.

name: Henpecked Husband
description: Each time you take a "Build Rooms" action with the second person you place, return the first person you placed home, unless it is on the "Meeting Place" action space.

name: Patch Caretaker
description: Each time you use an accumulation space while already having used another accumulation space for the same type of good that work phase, you also get 1 vegetable.

name: Luxurious Hostel
description: During scoring, if you then have more stone rooms than people, you get 4 bonus points. You can only use one card to get bonus points for your stone house.

name: Interim Storage
description: Each time you use a clay/reed/stone accumulation space, place 1 wood/clay/reed on this card. At the start of rounds 7, 11, and 14, move all the goods on this card to your supply.

name: Trimmer
description: In each work phase, after you enclose at least one farmyard space, you get 2 stone. (Subdividing an existing pasture does not count.)

name: Corf
description: Each time any player (including you) takes at least 3 stone from an accumulation space, you get 1 stone from the general supply.

name: Clay Deposit
description: Immediately after each time you use a clay accumulation space, you can exchange 1 clay for 1 bonus point. If you do, place the clay on the accumulation space.

name: Master Workman
description: Each time before you use an action space card on round spaces 1/2/3/4, you get 1 wood/clay/reed/stone.

name: Pet Grower
description: Each time you use an animal accumulation space, if afterward you have no animal in your house, you also get 1 sheep.

name: Knapper
description: Each time before you use an action space card on round spaces 5 to 7, you get 1 stone.

name: Pure Breeder
description: You immediately get 1 wood. After each round that does not end with a harvest, you can breed exactly one type of animal. (This is not considered a breeding phase.)

name: Game Provider
description: Immediately before each harvest, you can discard 1/3/4 grain from different fields to get 1/2/3 wild boars.

name: Wholesale Market
description: Place 1 food on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Brook
description: Each time you use one of the four action spaces above the "Fishing" accumulation space, you get 1 additional food.

name: Beaver Colony
description: From now on, one of your pastures with stable cannot hold animals. Each time you get reed from an action space, you get 1 bonus point.

name: Ox Skull
description: During scoring, if you have no cattle, you get 3 bonus points.

name: Stall Holder
description: Once per round, if you have 0/1/2/3/4 unfenced stables on your farm, you can exchange 2 grain for 1 bonus point and 1/2/3/4/5 food.

name: Sowing Director
description: Each time after another player uses the "Grain Utilization" action space, you get a "Sow" action.

name: Packaging Artist
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 grain. Each time you get a "Minor Improvement" action, you can take a "Bake Bread" action instead.

name: Agricultural Fertilizers
description: Each time after you turn at least 2 unused spaces into used spaces in one action, you get an additional "Sow" action.

name: Future Building Site
description: Up until all other farmyard spaces are used, you cannot use the unused spaces that are orthogonally adjacent to your house.

name: Rolling Pin
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have more clay than wood in your supply, you get 1 food.

name: Carpenter's Yard
description: You can build the "Joinery" and "Well" major improvement even when taking a "Minor Improvement" action, or you can build both with a single "Major Improvement" action.

name: Loppers
description: Each time you build 1 or more fences, you can also use this card to exchange 1 wood and 1 fence in your supply for 2 food and 1 bonus point.

name: Bargain Hunter
description: At the start of each round, you can place 1 food from your supply on the "Traveling Players" accumulation space to play a minor improvement by paying its cost.

name: Cattle Buyer
description: Each time another player uses the "Fencing" action space, you can buy exactly 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle from the general supply for 1/2/2 food.

name: Craftsmanship Promoter
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 stone. You can build any of the major improvements in the bottom row of the supply board even when taking a "Minor Improvement" action.

name: Pan Baker
description: Each time you use the "Grain Utilization" action space, you also get 2 clay and 1 wood.

name: Cob
description: At the start of each work phase, if you have at least 1 clay in your supply, you can exchange exactly 1 grain for 2 clay and 1 food.

name: Frame Builder
description: Each time you build a room/renovate, but only once per room/action, you can replace exactly 2 clay or 2 stone with 1 wood.

name: Cattle Whisperer
description: Add 5 and 8 to the current round and place 1 cattle on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the cattle.

name: Sheep Whisperer
description: Add 2, 5, 8, and 10 to the current round and place 1 sheep on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the sheep.

name: Food Merchant
description: For each grain you harvest from a field, you can buy 1 vegetable for 3 food. If you harvest the last grain from a field, the vegatble costs you only 2 food.

name: Inner Districts Director
description: Each time you use the "Forest" or "Clay Pit" accumulation space, you can place 1 stone from the general supply on the other space. If you do, you can immediately place another person.

name: Building Tycoon
description: Each time after another player builds 1 or more rooms, you can give them 1 food to build exactly 1 room yourself. (You must pay the building cost of the room.)

name: Basket
description: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can exchange 2 wood for 3 food. If you do, place those 2 wood on the accumulation space.

name: Sowing Master
description: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 wood. Each time after you use an action space with the "Sow" action, you get 2 food.

name: Silage
description: In each returning home phase after which there is no harvest, you can pay exactly 1 grain‚Äîeven from a field-to breed exactly one type of animal.

name: Abort Oriel
description: You can no longer play this card when any player (including you) has 5 or more cards in front of them.

name: Corn Schnapps Distillery
description: Once per round, you can pay 1 grain to place 1 food on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Butler
description: If you play this card in round 11 or before, during scoring, you get 4 bonus points if you then have more rooms than people.

name: Cookery Lesson
description: Each time you use a "Lesson" action space and a cooking improvement on the same turn, you get 1 bonus point.

name: Stone Importer
description: In the breeding phase of the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th/6th harvest, you can use this card to buy exactly 2 stone for 2/2/3/3/4/1 food.

name: Ravenous Hunger
description: Immediately after each time you use the "Vegetable Seeds" action space, you can place another person on an accumulation space and get 1 additional good of the accumulating type.

name: Wall Builder
description: Each time you build at least 1 room, you can place 1 food on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Material Deliveryman
description: Each time any player (including you) takes 5/6/7/8+ goods from an accumulation space, you get 1 wood/clay/reed/stone from the general supply.

name: Pioneering Spirit
description: This card is an action space for you only. In rounds 3-5, it provides a "renovation" action. In rounds 6-8, it provides your choice of 1 vegetable, wild boar, or cattle.

name: Motivator
description: On your first turn each round, if you have no unused farmyard spaces, you can place a person from your supply.

name: Godly Spouse
description: Each time you take a "Family Growth" action with the second person you place in a round, return the first person you placed home.

name: Trellises
description: Immediately place 1 food on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of fences you have built. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Brotherly Love
description: As long as you have exactly 4 people, in the work phase of each round, you can place your third and fourth person immediately after one another, even on the same action space.

name: Joiner of the Sea
description: Each time another player uses the "Fishing"/"Reed Bank" accumulation space, you can give them 1 wood to get 2 food/3 food from the general supply.

name: Parrot Breeder
description: On your turn, if you pay 1 grain to the general supply, you can use the same action space that the player to your right has just used on their turn.

name: Facades Carving
description: When you play this card, you can exchange any number of food for 1 bonus point each, up to the number of completed harvests.
prerequisites: Wood in Your Supply >= Current Round

name: Wood Saw
description: Each time all other players have more people than you, you can take a "Build Rooms" action.

name: Grassland Harrow
description: Add 1 to the current round for each building resource in your supply and place 1 field on the corresponding round space. A the start of the round, you can plow the field.
prerequisites: 2 Occupations, 1 Building Resource in Your Supply

name: Garden Claw
description: Place 1 food on each remaining round space, up to three times the number of planted fields you have. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Silokeeper
description: Each time you use the action space card that has been revealed right before the most recent harvest, you also get 1 grain.

name: Slurry Spreader
description: In the field phase of each harvest, each time you take the last grain/vegetable from a field, you also get 2 food/1 food.

name: Elephantgrass Plant
description: Immediately after each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 reed for 1 bonus point.

name: Minstrel
description: At the start of each returning home phase, if only one action space card on round space 1 to 4 is unoccupied, you can use that action space.

name: Stagehand
description: Each time another player uses the "Traveling Players" accumulation space, you can take your choice of a "Build Fences", "Build Stables", or "Build Rooms" action.

name: Stable Milker
description: Each time you build at least 2 stables on the same turn, you also get 1 cattle.

name: Dwelling Mound
description: From now on, you must pay 1 food for each new field tile that you place in your farmyard.

name: Turnip Farmer
description: At the start of the returning home phase of each round, if both the "Day Laborer" and "Grain Seeds" action spaces are occupied, you get 1 vegetable.

name: Riverine Shepherd
description: Each time you use the "Sheep Market" or "Reed Bank" accumulation space, you can also take 1 good from the respective other accumulation space, if possible.

name: Master Renovator
description: At the end of the work phases of rounds 7 and 9, you can take a "Renovation" action without placing a person and pay 1 building resource of your choice less.

name: Furniture Carpenter
description: Each harvest, if any player (including you) owns the Joinery or an upgrade thereof, you can buy exactly 1 bonus point for 2 food.

name: Wool Blankets
description: During scoring, if you live in a wooden/clay/stone house by then, you get 3/2/0 bonus points.

name: Wood Worker
description: Each time you take wood from an accumulation space, you can exchange 1 wood for 1 sheep. Place the wood on the accumulation space.

name: Cookery Outfitter
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each cooking improvement you have.

name: Social Benefits
description: Immediately after the feeding phase of each harvest, if you have no food left, you get 1 wood and 1 clay.

name: Mill Wheel
description: Each time you use the "Grain Utilization" action space while the "Fishing" accumulation space is occupied, you get an additional 2 food.

name: Merchant
description: Immediately after each time you take a "Major or Minor Improvement" or "Minor Improvement" action, you can pay 1 food to take the action a second time.

name: Lifting Machine
description: At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you can move 1 vegetable from one of your fields to your supply. (This is not considered a field phase.)

name: Telegram
description: Add 1 to the current round for each fence in your supply and mark the corresponding round space. In that round only, you can place a person from your supply.

name: Dutch Windmill
description: Each time you take a "Bake Bread" action in a round immediately following a harvest, you get 3 additional food.

name: Visionary
description: If you play this card in round 4 or before, you get 1 stone, 1 vegetable, and 2 wild boar. You cannot grow your family until round 11, unless all other players already have.

name: Illusionist
description: Each time you use a building resource accumulation space, you can discard exactly 1 card from your hand to get 1 additional building resource of the accumulating type.

name: Wealthy Man
description: At the start of each of the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th/6th harvest, if you have at least 1/2/3/4/5/6 grain fields, you get 1 bonus point.

name: Pig Stalker
description: Each time you use an animal accumulation space, if you occupy either the action space immediately above or below that accumulation space, you also get 1 wild boar.

name: Sculpture
description: You can only play this card if there are more complete rounds left to play than you have unused farmyard spaces.

name: Reed Roof Renovator
description: Each time another player renovates, you immediately get 1 reed from the general supply. When you play this card in a 3-player game, you immediately get 1 reed.

name: Culinary Artist
description: Each time another player uses the "Traveling Players" accumulation space, you can exchange your choice of 1 grain/sheep/vegetable for 4/5/7 food.

name: Full Peasant
description: Each time after you use the "Grain Utilization" or "Fencing" action space while the other is unoccupied, you can pay 1 food to use the other space with the same person.

name: Canal Boatman
description: Each time you use "Fishing" or "Reed Bank", you can pay 1 food to immediately place another person on this card. If you do, you get your choice of 3 stone or 1 grain plus 1 vegetable.

name: Claw Knife
description: Each time you use the "Sheep Market" accumulation space, place 1 food on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Mummy's Boy
description: Once per round, when placing a person after your first two, you can place it on the action space with your 2nd person and use that space again. (Mark the action space).

name: Small Trader
description: Each time you take a "Major or Minor Improvement" action to play an improvement from your hand, you also get 3 food.

name: Cattle Farm
description: For each pasture you have, you can keep 1 cattle on this card.

name: Heart of Stone
description: Each time a "Quarry" accumulation space is revealed, if you have room in your house, you can immediately take a "Family Growth" action without placing a person.

name: Large-Scale Farmer
description: Each time after you use the "Farm Expansion" or "Major Improvement" action space while the other is unoccupied, you can pay 1 food to use that other space with the same person.

name: Forest Scientist
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if there is no wood left on the game board, you get 1 food‚Äîfrom round 5 on, even 2 food.

name: Clutterer
description: During scoring, you get 1 bonus point for each card played after this on that has "accumulation space(s)" in its text.

name: Oven Site
description: When you play this card, you get 2 wood and you can immediately build the "Clay Oven" or "Stone Oven" major improvement. Either way, it only costs you 1 clay and 1 stone.

name: Blackberry Farmer
description: Each time you build fences, place 1 food on each remaining round space, up to the number of fences just built. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Bean Counter
description: Each time you use an action space on round spaces 1 to 8, place 1 food on this card. Each time this cards has 3 food on it, move the food to your supply.

name: Riparian Builder
description: Each time another player uses the "Reed Bank" accumulation space, you can build a room: if you build a clay/stone room, you get a discount of 1 clay/2 stone.

name: Interior Decorator
description: Each time you renovate, place 1 food on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the food.

name: Twin Researcher
description: Each time you use one of the two accumulation spaces for the same type of good containing exactly the same number of goods, you can also buy 1 bonus point for 1 food.

name: Sugar Baker
description: Each time after you use the "Grain Utilization" action space, you can buy 1 bonus point for 1 food. Place the food on the action space (for the next visitor).

name: Forest Tallyman
description: Each time both the "Forest" and "Clay Pit" accumulation spaces are occupied, you can use the gap between them as an action space to get 2 clay and 3 wood.

name: Small Animal Breeder
description: Before the start of each round, if you have food equal to or higher than the current round number (e.g., 8+ food in round 8), you get 1 food.

name: Hardworking Man
description: This card is an action space for you only. If each other player has more rooms than you, it provides the "Day Laborer", "Building Rooms", and "Major Improvement" actions (all three).

name: Sequestrator
description: Place 3 reed and 4 clay on this card. The next player to have 3 pastures/5 field tiles get the 3 reed/4 clay (not retroactively).

name: Roughcaster
description: Each time you build at least 1 clay room or renovate your house from clay to stone, you also get 3 food.

name: Paymaster
description: Each time another player uses a food accumulation space, you can give them 1 grain from your supply to get 1 bonus point.

name: Forest Campaigner
description: Each time before you place a person, if there are at least 8 wood total on accumulation spaces, you get 1 food.

name: Catcher
description: Each time you place your 1st/2nd/3rd person in a round on a building resource accumulation space with exactly 5/4/3 building resources, you get 1 food.

name: Resource Analyzer
description: Before the start of each round, if you have more building resources than all other players of at least two types, you get 1 food.

name: Huntsman
description: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, you can pay 1 grain to get 1 wild boar.

name: Curator
description: In the returning home phase of each round, if you return at least 3 people from accumulation spaces, you can buy 1 bonus point for 1 food.

name: Cooperative Plower
description: Each time you use the "Farmland" action space while the "Grain Seeds" action space is occupied, you can plow 1 additional field.

name: Tree Inspector
description: This card is a "1 Wood" accumulation space for you only. Each time the newly revealed action space card is a "Quarry" accumulation space, you must discard all wood from this card.

name: Growing Farm
description: You can only play this card if you have at least as many pasture spaces as the number of completed rounds. If you do, you get a number of food equal to the current round.

name: Breeder Buyer
description: Each time you build at least 1 wood/clay/stone room and at least 1 stable on the same turn, you also get 1 sheep/wild boar/cattle.

name: Perennial Rye
description: Each round that does not end with a harvest, you can pay 1 grain to breed exactly 1 type of animal. (This is not considered a breeding phase.)

name: Loudmouth
description: Each time you take at least 4 building resources or 4 animals from an accumulation space, you also get 1 food.
